SIMPLE: fenian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fenian
<hw>Fe"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the
<ets>Finians</ets> or <ets>Fenii</ets>, the old militia of Ireland, who
were so called from <ets>Fin</ets> or <ets>Finn</ets>, <ets>Fionn</ets>,
or <ets>Fingal</ets>, a popular hero of Irish traditional
history.]</ety> <def>A member of a secret organization, consisting
mainly of Irishmen, having for its aim the overthrow of English rule in
Ireland.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fenian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fenian
<hw>Fe"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to Fenians
or to Fenianism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fenianism</ent>⟦br⟧
